title: locked files and recursing paths
body:
sorry if this is the wrong place for this report -- please direct me to the proper place if so

### Issue Description
In almost every .Net Core project I work on now, I frequently get locked files.  Usually it's just warnings (it waits and retries), but I still often need to restart VS Code, manually delete all bin and obj folders, or even restart Windows to get things unlocked.

Today specifically, I received a locked file warning with a recursive path.  I have seen this once before and it went away when I cleared all my bin and obj folders.

### Steps to Reproduce
1. open a Razor Pages project in vscode
2. start debugging (F5)
3. build outputs a series of warnings that dll files are locked, retries a few times and then succeeds
4.  occassionally, the path of the file that is locked has "bin\Debug
et6.0" repeated in its path many times as below

### Expected Behavior
1. dll and other content files are not locked
2. warnings are not displayed in build output
3. paths of supposedly locked files don't include a recursive (and non-existent) path

I am including some json files in an xunit project using the following syntax in the csproj file:
```
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="**\*.json">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>Always</CopyToOutputDirectory>
    </Content>  
  </ItemGroup>
```

The .NET SDK defines a property you can use to avoid this (and uses it for its own default includes):

```diff
-    <Content Include="**\*.json">

```
